Som Bunnarith We hear from the male survivor of an acid attack in Cambodia about how a support group helped him to turn his life around and find work again. Jordanian wine We meet Omar Zumot, a Jordanian wine producer whose vineyards are a true labour of love and whose wine is winning international awards. Our Billie Ian Clayton lost his nine year old daughter Billie in a canoeing accident, in which he was only able to save her twin brother. He tells Roger Hearing how the family has come to terms with Billie's death and how writing a tribute to her has helped his grief. Ian Clayton's book "Our Billie" is published by Penguin in the UK. Show less